Let $\mathbf{d} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \times \begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 0 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$. We can compute the cross product of vectors $\mathbf{a}$ and $\mathbf{b}$ by using the formula

\begin{align*}
\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b} & = \begin{pmatrix} a_2b_3 - a_3b_2 \\ a_3b_1 - a_1b_3 \\ a_1b_2 - a_2b_1 \end{pmatrix} \\
& = \begin{pmatrix} (1)(1) - (0)(0) \\ (0)(0) - (2)(1) \\ (2)(0) - (1)(0) \end{pmatrix} \\
& = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}.
\end{align*}

So, we have $\mathbf{d} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}.$ <end think>
